		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Zack S wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">It should also greatly simplify the code required to make this work. Each byte of data will correspond to exactly 2 symbols. Not to mention the lack of entry screen.</div>
<br />With 4 symbols, you can convey 2 bits of information: 00, 01, 10, 11. You need four of those for eight bits of data, i.e. a byte.
<br />To convey 10 bytes of data (80 bits), you need 40 of those arrows. It gets tedious, especially when writing them down.

		

		</td>
