		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I'd argue that with 4 symbols the amount of time inputting would be quite close to just entering your custom control scheme via a prefs screen.
<br />
<br />Limiting the amount of options the end user wades through IS a noble goal though.
<br />
<br />What about a cross shaped control that rests at 35 in the middle.  Vertical movement is in the tens place and horizontal is in the ones place: 
<br />
<br />65
<br />55
<br />45
<br />|35| &lt;- Middle
<br />25
<br />15
<br />5
<br />
<br />and starts at 35 horizontally:
<br />
<br />30-31-32-33-34 |35| &lt;-Middle 36-37-38-39-40
<br />
<br />Worst case scenario it takes 8 key presses to reach 0 (3 down + 5 left)
<br />
<br />I know this is virtually the same as a symbol chart but maybe snapping back to the middle value would save some input time?

		

